subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax.
Slightly shiny, with light brown spots (
Figs. 1
A–B). Pronotum in dorsal view long and wide, with lateral margin slightly sinuous; lobe of pronotum with dorsal margin nearly straight, slightly convex at ventral margin (
Fig. 1B
). Mesonotum rectangular in dorsal view, 2.5 times shorter than pronotum and 1.2 times shorter than metanotum, with lateroapical margins projected over metanotum (
Fig. 1B
). Metanotum trapezoidal in dorsal view, with basal margin wider than apical margin (
Fig. 1B
).

Abdomen.
Supra anal plate with apical margin arched, slightly sinuous (
Fig. 3D
). Cercus with homogenous width until abruptly narrowing at apical third (
Fig. 3
C–E). Subgenital plate subtriangular, with lateral margin gradually narrowing towards apex, apical margin arched (
Fig. 3C
). Ovipositor dark brown, shiny, slender, conspicuously arched, slightly pointed dorsally, with rounded apex (
Fig. 3E
).

Environmental notes.
The specimens were collected in a tropical rainforest (
Holdridge 1996
). The locality “Reserva Natural y Ecoturistica Las Dalias” is located in a relic of secondary forest, on the banks of the “La Cajona” stream, the specific collection site is composed of forest and herbaceous vegetation. The Locality of the “Finca El Limón” is on the banks of the “La Morrocoya” stream, where the predominant vegetation are bushes. The locality “Vereda Aguas Negras” is part of a riparian forest on the “La Perdiz” stream. All the specimens were found near water bodies (
Fig. 4A
) and in flooded areas (
Fig. 4B
).
